reviews.text: The food was delicious. So much to choose from. Specialty pizzas, traditional and specialty pasta dishes, appetizers, baked stuffed potatoes, main entrees, sandwiches, soups, salads and desserts. Freshly baked sourdough bread while you wait for your food. As you enter you see them making the pizzas with fresh ingredients and smells so delicious. The staff is friendly and make your dinning experience very enjoyable. They make you feel like family and so welcoming. This is definitely my go to location when I'm in San Francisco!!!!

Although you can't say this is a place with fancy atmosphere, it's very fun and all the locals come and lots of families and it's very cheerful and happy. So I gave it five stars. The food is great. The place is very basic but very very good. There's nothing fancy about the Parmesan cheese but some of the pastas are amazing and very unusual and very very good. The baked pastas are especially good. The salads again are nothing fancy but are actually really delicious and well made. The garden salad is full of fresh vegetables with red onion and tomato and the antipasto salad is awesome. I just discovered the Greek Caesar which is extremely delicious. The pasta carbonara is the best I've ever eaten anywhere and they have something unique that they call all a Louisiana which is kind of a Cajun Creole sort of thing with large prawns and pretty spicy. I would highly recommend that too. And the linguine with fresh clams is excellent. And of course their pizza's really famous and has been around for almost 75 years now.

We came here super late for dinner after a concert and had the best service and food. They were really busy but still super quick. The sunset pizza was awesome and the guy who seemed to be running it (he said his dad opened it in 1958 IIRC) was super friendly and gave us great recs.

Fast, friendly service. No frills, high quality Italian food. Kid and family friendly. Been coming here for decades and the quality has always remained high. Great pizzas. Great pastas. They cook the shrimp in their pasta to perfection!!

Reminds me of Chicago thin crust, my absolute favorite style.  Vibrant red pizza sauce, some of the best Italian sausage I have had as well.  Crispy crust, nicely seasoned, and snappy to get to the table.

Pasquale's grandson was our server, the absolute nicest young man.  I hope he gets this restaurant someday, he cares a lot about it.  Sorry no photo, ate it too fast.

editorial_summary.overview: Hand-tossed pizzas, Italian entrees & red-sauce pastas make up the menu at this circa-1961 spot.

detailedReviews.text: This used to be my favorite pizza place in the whole city! Unfortunately no more... Recently I had ordered two xl pizzas and both were completely burned on the bottom when I got home. When I called the place to request a refund or a new pizza, I got yelled at by a rude lady who was in charge of the shift working there. She tried to suggest that it was my fault somehow that I didn't let the staff know earlier that the pizzas were uneatable. The staff that works there does not know how to make a decent pizza and for the money they charge to be incapable to even make sure that it's not burned when it's packed, is quite ridiculous! Yet, even more ridiculous that instead of taking ownership of the issue and fixing it as well as hiring some competent staff, the manager would yell at the customer. Really?! I won't be going there that's for sure!
